subject: Last chance to vote for QS keyboard map!

messageBody:
If you have not done so, please consider voting in this poll (see
below). I set up the poll to close at the end of February--I don't
know what time zone will be used to close the poll, but there is still
time.

At the moment only 11 members out of 345 have voted. It is currently a
tie between Peter Guiness's proposal and the QS-B proposal, so every
vote counts!

Thanks.

Ted


---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: <Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com>
Date: 1 Feb 2008 21:04:11 -0000
Subject: [Read_Alphabet] New poll for Read_Alphabet
To: Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com

Enter your vote today! A new poll has been created for the
Read_Alphabet group:

Please vote for your preference for a new ASCII key map for the Read
Alphabet, from among the proposals included in the file
'qs_keybd_proposals3.csv' in the 'Files->Key mapping proposals' folder
on the group website.

The purpose of this vote is to establish a standard for font
developers to implement in keyboard assignments, and to facilitate the
exchange of Quickscript in email and in plain text documents.

The scope of the proposals includes the 40 core letters of the
alphabet, the four alternate letters, the two letters used for
Scottish, Welsh and Irish place names, and the three punctuation marks
unique to this alphabet. Some proposals also include the eight
half-letters. In order to be considered, the proposals were required
to assign all free-standing Quickscript letters to upper case or lower
case Roman letters. (There are not enough letters in the Roman
alphabet to maintain this requirement for all of the half-letters.)
Since the Jerome keyboard map does not meet this requirement, and
proposals for a minimal update of the Jerome map gained no support in
group discussion, it is not included among the final candidates.

This poll will close at the end of February 2008.

Thank you for voting!

Ted Larson Freeman


o QS-SAMPA
o Peter Guinness's proposal
o QS-B
o QS-Nu
o Moira O'Brien's proposal

To vote, please visit the following web page:
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/surveys?id=2650278

Note: Please do not reply to this message. Poll votes are not
collected via email. To vote, you must go to the Yahoo! Groups web
site listed above.

Thanks!
